message.content: Most men in Kiribati hold negative views towards divorce. They generally believe that divorce is a shameful and unacceptable act that goes against their cultural and religious values. Men in Kiribati prioritize maintaining strong family bonds and view divorce as a failure to fulfill their responsibilities as husbands and fathers. They often perceive divorce as a sign of weakness and lack of commitment, and consider it as a disruption to the social fabric of their society.
